    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six powerplant. This high-revving unit utilizes individual throttle bodies and dual VANOS variable valve timing to deliver linear power delivery up to its 8,000 RPM redline. Power is channeled through a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission to the rear wheels via an M Variable Differential Lock. The chassis remains taut, benefiting from a proactive subframe reinforcement and recent trailing arm bushing replacements. The suspension maintains factory-spec damping, providing exceptional lateral grip and highly communicative steering feedback through the rack-and-pinion setup. This example has been meticulously maintained with a documented service history addressing the rod bearings and cooling system. While it shows honest patina from spirited use, the mechanical synchronization and drivetrain integrity are superb, making it a quintessential driver's tool.",
